creator: Johann Karl August Musäus
description:
LibriVox recording of Libussa by Johann Karl August Musäus. (Translated by John Oxenford.)
Read in English by Crln Yldz Ksr
This is the Tale of Libussa, the mythical founder of the city of Prague. It chronicles the story of her parents and her birth, her elevation to the throne of Bohemia, and how she must fight for her true love. Musäus' famous version of the story is marked by the special poetry of his language and the beautiful, compelling setting and atmosphere. - Summary by Carolin
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
